cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method to train machine learning algorithms on data samples with background described by sPlot. This involves dealing with negative weights, which can cause issues with some machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with analyzing data samples, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a mathematically rigorous way to train machine learning algorithms, which could also place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
